review_title: ummm NO. Simply NO NO NO.
one_reviews_text: How is this even a game/app? It does nothing. Nothing i Tell you. NOTHING... Dont install it. You have allready wasted enough time just reading this review. ...
I didn't see a thing,bugged app sucks for right now. Bummer :(
I've tried multiple times to load this but after showing the menu and trying to load a home it just goes blank..
I just see aloading screen the lasts forever.  I waited 15 min and it never loaded.  I have retried multiple times - just waiting to load.

This should've been labeled as a midget simulator. I felt like Bilbo Baggins staring at a light switch the size of my face. 
When I think VR I think of hip, techie, bright lights, new age, etc. When they made this I have no idea who their target audience they were aiming for because there are a couple large houses that didn't have a TV and the decor was from a Norman Rockwell painting. If they were aiming for 60-90 year olds you lost them because there are some spots where you think you're going to teleport to another part of the room only to get dragged through a wall like the movie Ghost to be put outside. 

Rename this Paranormal Hobbit Paradox Sleep Aid and it might get better results.

Houses, offices - scale is important. If you get it right, VR visit will be almost like being there. Otherwise it's just a baby step towards that goal. 

Nevertheless this is already surprisingly enjoyable so 3 stars as motivation to get where this should be (including depth).

Feels like I'm in a bubble of a planetarium looking at flat picture.  It definitly beats looking at flat pictures, but not by much.  Once SLAM technology becomes more prevalent, these houses will be 3D mapped and modeled through quick, passing scans.  But until then, this is about as good as you'll get next to visiting the place or seeing it via video.

Although this app has stiff competition from the other VR app "Transported," it is able to set itself apart. There are 3 ways to explore each home listing: selecting circles to teleport, floorplan, and rooms. Unfortunately, the teleportation is difficult to navigate as you never know where you'll end up and sometimes it even takes you backwards when it should be taking you forwards. The limited home listings (~20 homes and offices) is good enough to show the potential for this app. Without a wider selection, it is merely for artistic purposes at this time.
